comment_data.body:
Any reason not to call `client:stop` in this case? Users can start clients without going through lsp.config/enable and we already got the client object here.

E.g. my custom `LspStop` is currently:

```lua
  api.nvim_create_user_command(
    'LspStop',
    function(kwargs)
      local name = kwargs.fargs[1]
      for _, client in ipairs(lsp.get_clients({ name = name })) do
        client:stop()
      end
    end,
    {
      nargs = "?",
      complete = function()
        return vim.tbl_map(function(c) return c.name end, lsp.get_clients())
      end
    }
  )
```


(Also raises a bit the question if `:lsp stop` is  "stop server" or "stop and disable server")
